abstract: In March, talk of victory was in the air. Now, maintaining unity against President Vladimir V. Putin is looking harder, with President Biden heading to Germany and Spain to rally Europe.
snippet: In March, talk of victory was in the air. Now, maintaining unity against President Vladimir V. Putin is looking harder, with President Biden heading to Germany and Spain to rally Europe.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When President Biden met his Western allies in Europe three months ago, the world was rallying behind Ukraine, and NATO suddenly had a new sense of purpose — its old purpose, containing Russia. There was talk of “crippling sanctions.” President Vladimir V. Putin was in retreat, and talk of victory was in the air.

main: A New Task for Biden: Readying Allies for a Long Conflict in Ukraine
print_headline: Biden’s New Task: Bracing Europe for Another ‘Long, Twilight Struggle’

abstract: The Crimean Peninsula, which Russia seized in 2014, has been a staging ground for other attacks and an increasingly attractive target for Ukraine.
snippet: The Crimean Peninsula, which Russia seized in 2014, has been a staging ground for other attacks and an increasingly attractive target for Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — As swarms of Russian soldiers stormed Ukrainian lines in furious assaults around two cities in the east on Tuesday, Ukraine set the stage for its own advance by making strikes deep behind Russian lines, including what appeared to be a drone attack on a vital logistical hub in the occupied Crimean Peninsula.

main: Its Forces Under Siege, Ukraine Hits Distant, Russian-Held Crimea
print_headline: Its Forces Under Siege, Ukraine Hits Russian-Held Crimea

abstract: The U.S.-brokered deal has stirred fierce debate in Israel between some who view it as an achievement and others as a dangerous capitulation.
snippet: The U.S.-brokered deal has stirred fierce debate in Israel between some who view it as an achievement and others as a dangerous capitulation.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Israel and Lebanon, neighboring countries still technically at war, signed an American-brokered agreement on Thursday demarcating a joint maritime border and regulating their rights to gas reserves at sea. The move came amid a bitter debate in Israel over the terms of the deal and its chances of reducing — or, conversely, fanning — future conflict.

main: Israeli-Lebanese Maritime Deal Marks a Milestone, With Limitations
print_headline: Israel and Lebanon Sign  Deal on Maritime Border

abstract: Their answers gave me hope for the future of our species.
snippet: Their answers gave me hope for the future of our species.
lead_paragraph: If artificial intelligence were going to cause mass unemployment, you would expect to see it happen first in the tech sector, where A.I. excels. To take just one example, ChatGPT is pretty good (not perfect) at generating code, fixing bugs and even building a website — doing in a few seconds what might take hours for a human programmer. Why bother hiring a person who has learned to think like a computer when you can employ a computer that thinks like a computer?

main: Four Experts on Tech Hiring Talk About Where the Jobs Are

abstract: President Biden’s remarks reflect the urgent concern in Washington and among Western allies that Russia may be searching for a pretext to unleash a battlefield nuclear weapon.
snippet: President Biden’s remarks reflect the urgent concern in Washington and among Western allies that Russia may be searching for a pretext to unleash a battlefield nuclear weapon.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Biden renewed his warning to President Vladimir V. Putin on Tuesday that it would be an “incredibly serious mistake” to use a tactical nuclear weapon in Ukraine, reflecting the increasingly urgent concern in Washington and among Western allies that Russia may be searching for a pretext to unleash such a weapon.

main: Biden Says Russian Use of a Nuclear Weapon Would Be a ‘Serious Mistake’
print_headline: Biden Tells Russia Use of Nuclear Arms Would Be ‘Serious Mistake’
